				<td rowspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" style="text-align: justify;" width="100%" valign=top>
				<div><br><blockquote><hr>Merloc-DEV wrote:<br><div>Hello Everyone,</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>Before I get too far along, I thought I'd ask for some feedback from players on how they view different stats with respect to the class(es) they play.&nbsp; Obviously, I have my own view on things, but I'd like to know how any why people have their own views.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>What I'd like, is for you to&nbsp;take a look at this list of the basic item stats (feel free to include any others that I left out), and let me know how and why they think they are, or aren't, important to your class.&nbsp; All comments are useful, and feel free to use current items as examples to illustrate your points if you feel the need.&nbsp; Be sure to INCLUDE THE CLASS name, so I can put your feedback in context.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>Hopefully, I'll gain some new insights that will help me do my job better.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>Thanks.</div>
<br><hr></blockquote><br><br>You sure you know what your getting in to?&nbsp; As a Anguish geared Ranger and Shaman (and played a mage twink quite a bit) I just have a few general suggestions.&nbsp; Now, my biggest grip in itemization goes along with a items spell focus effects, but there are other issues.<br><br><br>First, look at the itemization of Vex Thal as an example of end zone itemization.&nbsp; Not only did it have a distinct mix of useful and unique items, there was also the lack of weapons which made it worthwhile.&nbsp; It was, and still is, the best itemized end expansion zone in EQ.<br><br>Second, class only items were cool when they first came out in PoP.&nbsp; But by now, with melee using their Epic 2/2.5 and non-melee having to give up their epics to wield (clerics excepted), they have become a waste.&nbsp; Getting 2x necro dagger (Dagger of Death)&nbsp; on ever 2 out of 3 Yihist kills in Tacvi is a beyond ridiculus.&nbsp; Additionally, go4ing to the OoW expansion itemization, beastlords made out.&nbsp; Not only did they get a Bst only 2hander from MPG trials, but they Bst only 1hander off Ture which is a carbon copy of the War/Rang/Rog/Bard/Monk/Bst 1 handed blunt off KtH (along with their Epic).&nbsp; This kind of itemization is pure laziness.<br><br>Third, a class like a shaman or druid is extremly dependent on their gears focus effects.&nbsp; Due to both the offensive and defensive nature of these classes, they need to have focus effects of just about every type.&nbsp; This includes:<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; healing focus<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; beneficial mana preservation<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; detrimental mana preservation<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; beneficial spell haste<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; detrimental spell haste<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; beneficial buff duration<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; detrimental debuff/dot duration<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; beneficial spell range (for heals)<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; detrimental spell range (more for druid nukes)<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Damage focus for shaman includes<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;  Magic (DoTs)<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;  Poison (DDs, Rains, AEs, DoTs)<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;  Cold (DD)<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Damage focus for druids includes<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; Fire<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;  Cold<br><br>In PoP is wasnt too difficult to fill in a focus needs.&nbsp; This is because you had spell Focus that covered more then one line.&nbsp; Conservation of Xegony covered both bene and detri mana pres.&nbsp; Fury of Solusek covered all DDs (I dont believe DoT focus was in the game at this point).&nbsp; <br><br>But now, equiping a shaman has problems in items with different needed focus effects taking the same slot.&nbsp; If I want beneficial mana preservation (Avariciousness of the Ikaav) and I'm in a Anguish level guild (so Anguish minus OMM, Tacvi including Tunat, DoN through YarLir, DoDH - Shyra/Bloodeye) I have limited choices.&nbsp; They include the BP from Tunat, boots from MPG Trial of Adaptation (which isnt normally farmed), the Ring of Deterance from AMV in Ang, the Shroud of Surging Storm from Yarlir (very rare drop, think we have gotten 3 in 30kills).&nbsp; Now, if I got the MPG trial boots then I cant use Anguish boots which has Beneficial Mana pres.&nbsp; So I have to get that from somewhere else.&nbsp; If I wanted posion damage focus, for which there is only one gear option between the Tacvi/MPG level loot and Demi-plane, that being the Eye of Rikk from Rikk.&nbsp; This is a Range so this would force me to drop my Crystal staff which would force me to get a detrimental mana pres somewhere else.&nbsp; The Warbeads of the Magus are nice but then I would loose my beneficial spell haste from 
  Necklace of Grimspirit Beads.&nbsp; So I have to find something else for that.<br><br>What I'm trying to point out here is casters have run into a jigsaw puzzle of items when they need to weigh Spell focus + item focus.&nbsp; Melee dont have to worry about this as Haste or ImpDodge or other melee centric needs dont denegrate and are not as needed.&nbsp; Additionally, for haste, a melee can just xp in a Skylance instance and wait for a 75HP/75mana/40%haste aug to drop...then they never have to worry about haste again.<br><br>Additionally, there are items in the game that make no sense or are just badly itemized.&nbsp; <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=47281" target=_blank>Belt of Contempt</a> for example off Ture.&nbsp; Its All/All but the focus effect applies to 3 classes (Shaman, SK, Necro) and of those 3, the shaman disease dots are worthless in a raid enviroment (and in general IMO).&nbsp; So you now have a All/all item which is just stats to almost all classes.&nbsp; Or shielding on Int caster only items (or even class items).&nbsp; The Mage head item from Qvic has 1% shielding on it.&nbsp; As a int caster, if they are getting hit, then shielding wont do them any good due to their crap AC and mitigation.&nbsp; Bracer of Grievous Harm
      from Tacvi has Fire damage focus on it.&nbsp; Since only Druids can use fire dmg of the 3 leather classes, its a useless focus for Beastlords; had the item had Cold dmg focus, then it would have been better itemized for the Leather Classes.&nbsp;&nbsp; Or Xxeric's Warbraid having Poison damage focus.&nbsp; Even though this item is for int casters, only Necros gain the benefit of the focus.&nbsp; If the Focus were fire, then 3 of the 4 classes could use...even better had the focus been magic based dmg, then every class who could wear could use.&nbsp; Finally, there are some caste only items that look like they were designed for melee only (think haste, atk and accuracy on a int caster item).<br><br>HP Regeneration.&nbsp; This as a whole needs to be rethought.&nbsp; Worn Regen has increased on a gradual level while Mob DPS and AE damage has increased on a exponential level.&nbsp; Whats wrong with players having a worn regen of 150/tic at the end game?&nbsp;&nbsp; Will this really unbalance the game?<br><br>Worn Attack - This is similar to the regen as it has diminished returns also.&nbsp; When you get to 2500+ attack, even the 50more attack from AAs wont make a difference in DPS.&nbsp; Also, this is another issue in that why do caster only gear have attack when casters rarely if ever melee a mob.<br><br>Dmg/Delay on weapons.&nbsp; For the most part, I have no issues here.&nbsp; The main one are piercing drops.&nbsp; For any class other then a rogue (and none epic2/2.5 rogu at that) to be using a poker is someone decreasing their DPS.&nbsp; When desiging pokers, look back at a <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=70710" target=_blank>Crystal Dagger</a> for inspiration.&nbsp; Also on the King/Queen in RS loot table is a <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=70721" target=_blank>Allin's Mace</a> and <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=70722" target=_blank>Crystal Hilted Shinai.</a>&nbsp; In this case, the dagge has a dmg/delay reasonable close to the other weapons (.7 vs .65).&nbsp; Yet a <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=47317" target=_blank>Aneuk Dagger of Eye Gouging</a> from Jelvin has a ratio of .82 making it all but worthless for non-rogues or Apps.&nbsp; The same goes <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=71645" target=_blank>Fang of Kessdona</a> (.8 ratio).&nbsp; Again a item that goes to either non epic2 rogues or to recruits.&nbsp; <br><br>There are several other issues which I'm sure others will point out, but this gives you an idea.<br></div>
				
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
