<DIV></DIV>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV>Class:&nbsp; Shaman</DIV>
<DIV>Level:&nbsp; 70</DIV>
<DIV>AA:&nbsp; 492&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Location:&nbsp; Tier 1 Demiplane of Blood</DIV>
<DIV>Function:&nbsp; Hardcore raider, not much in the way of grouping anymore</DIV>
<DIV>Role on Raids:&nbsp; Group healer, add DPS to melees when possible</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Magelo:&nbsp; <A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=833082" target=_blank>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=833082</A></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<UL>
<LI>HP:&nbsp; 10100&nbsp;&nbsp;Mana:&nbsp; 10969&nbsp; AC:&nbsp; 2332&nbsp; Attack:&nbsp; 1516</LI>
<LI>PR:&nbsp; 384&nbsp; MR:&nbsp; 409&nbsp; DR:&nbsp; 383&nbsp; FR:&nbsp; 446&nbsp; CR:&nbsp; 403</LI>
<LI>Have Epic 1.0, 1.5 and 2.0</LI>
<LI>HP Regen:&nbsp; 44/47&nbsp; Mana Regen:&nbsp; 31&nbsp; Damage Shield:&nbsp; 18</LI>
<LI>Avoidance:&nbsp; 98&nbsp; Accuracy:&nbsp; 50&nbsp; Spell Shield:&nbsp; 29&nbsp; Shielding:&nbsp; 18&nbsp; Stun Resist:&nbsp; 9&nbsp; Strikethrough:&nbsp; 10&nbsp; Combat&nbsp;Effects:&nbsp; 3&nbsp; DoT Shielding:&nbsp; 28&nbsp;</LI></UL>
<P></P>
<HR>

<DIV>HP:&nbsp; Extremely important<BR>Endurance:&nbsp; Not important to my class</DIV>
<DIV>AC: Extremely important</DIV>
<DIV>HP Regen:&nbsp; Important<BR>Mana Regen:&nbsp; Important if not maxed<BR>Endurance Regen:&nbsp; Not important to my class, on raids, melee with crap endurance regen holds us up more than anything after a wipe</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Strength:&nbsp; If not maxed, important<BR>Stamina:&nbsp; If not maxed, extremely important<BR>Agility:&nbsp; Not that important<BR>Dexterity:&nbsp; Minorly important<BR>Charisma:&nbsp; Up to max merchant sale value, minorly important; after that, not important<BR>Intelligence:&nbsp; Not important<BR>Wisdom:&nbsp; Important, if not maxed, extremely important</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Cold Resist:&nbsp; Extremely important<BR>Disease Resist:&nbsp; Extremely important<BR>Poison Resist:&nbsp; Extremely important<BR>Magic Resist:&nbsp; Extremely important<BR>Fire Resist:&nbsp; Extremely important</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Attack:&nbsp; Not important, but oddly, I am #1 on EQRankings for shaman attack by over 100 points on the Tribunal server<BR>Delay:&nbsp; When I solo stuff that's shaman tankable, it's nice, but not that important<BR>Damage:&nbsp; When I solo stuff that's shaman tankable, it's important<BR>Range:&nbsp; Not important - potion throwing was a nice idea, but it's not really useable every day in practice</DIV>
<DIV>Haste:&nbsp; When I solo stuff that's shaman tankable, it's important</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Combat Effects:&nbsp; Not important<BR>Shielding: Extremely important, hard to find on chain gear<BR>Stun Resist:&nbsp; Extremely important, wish it actually did more<BR>Strikethrough:&nbsp; Not important<BR>Spell Shield:&nbsp; Extremely important<BR>Avoidance:&nbsp; If not maxed, Extremely important, easy to max on chain gear<BR>Accuracy:&nbsp; Not important<BR>DOT Shielding:&nbsp; Extremely important</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Skill Mods:&nbsp; Wish they were on more gear.&nbsp; CoA hat is nice for the alteration bonus, Dodge +8% doesn't equal much for a shaman, but I have it<BR>Click Effects:&nbsp; I have a lot and use many in day-to-day play while soloing, grouping or raiding<BR>Proc Effects:&nbsp; Shaman procs are not very well done, we need more items with better ProcRateMods on them, currently clerics are the best priest at melee procs/defensive damage shields, heal the best and have a worthwhile skill (bash) than the other priests.<BR>Worn Effects:&nbsp; A lot of my current gear has these and I like them, wish Improved Dodge 3 did more, it is around maybe a 1-2% increase for a shaman with max defense/stats/avoidance/dodge/dodge +%<BR>Focus Effects:&nbsp; See below, extremely important</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Kanamori Diestoomuch</DIV>
<DIV>70 Shammyknight (yes, I want to be able to live through 2 rounds of trash again)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><BR>Here is my rant I posted on an itemization thread recently.&nbsp; The jist is shaman focus effects are craptacularily itemized.&nbsp; Try to get all your focus effects is difficult, since stuff is all over the place.&nbsp; If a focus effect stays on one single slot (ie legs or arms or somewhere) for 2 consecutive expansions, I'd be impressed.&nbsp; Also, since GoD, shamans have had the shaft compared to necromancers for focus effects, especially since our main modes of DPS are the same.&nbsp; I'm not asking to DPS like a necro, but getting the proper focuses for the 2 classes is way out of balance.</P>
<P><BR>&nbsp;</P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Kanamori wrote:<BR>
<DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>On that, I'd like to propose that shaman focus distribution is teh suck (at least referring to DPoB-level, haven't gotten too far into PoR).&nbsp; If you can compare two classes, necromancer and shaman, it is infinately harder to get the focuses you want (hi2u poison) versus the ones you don't need (hi2u fire, disease, etc...).&nbsp; Now, my knowledge of PoR-level stuff isn't that high, but it seems to continue.&nbsp; To get the CoA/DoN-level poison focus for necro's it's a common raid item, for shaman, you have to make a last-blood/bazu augment.&nbsp; Bit of a difference there.</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>40%&nbsp;(Murk Venom)</STRONG> - <EM>Eye of Rikkukin</EM> drops off Rikkukin the Defender in DoN for a shaman; the comparable item for necros is <EM>Xxeric's Warbraid</EM> which drops in Tacvi (INT Caster only, but the other 3 have no poison abilities at all, thus NEC preferred).</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>45% (Venom of Anguish)</STRONG> - no lootable items for shaman (can make a <EM>Bazu Seal of Poison</EM> for the effect, thus DoD-era); the comparable item for necros is <EM>Blightbringer's Pants of the Grave</EM>, which is the Tier 2 CoA Silk legs quest item (NEC only).</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>50% (Dragon Bile)</STRONG> - no lootable items for shaman (can make a <EM>Last Blood of the Assassin</EM> for the effect, thus DPoB/PoR-era); the comparable item for necros is <EM>Mark of the Grave Finder</EM>, which is the mask quest from DoN (NEC only).</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>60% (Vampiric Malady/Bile? which is it SoE/Lucy/Allakhazam?)</STRONG> - <EM>Choker of Unspoken Lies</EM> from DPoB (Preist and INT Casters) for a shaman (note, it's a neck item which are hard to upgrade, thus competition is very high); the comparable item for necros (besides the same neck as a shaman) is <EM>Azure Breeches of the Diplomat</EM> from DPoB (INT Caster only, but the other 3 have no poison abilities at all, thus NEC preferred).</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>65% (Okahn's Blood)</STRONG> - <EM>Three Octave Shawl</EM> (ALL except WAR, PAL, MNK, BRD, ROG and BER, another highly contested item), somewhere in PoR.</DIV></DIV></DIV><BR>
